    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A process by which an object is removed or detached from its original context and introduced into the collection of a museum, leading to an alteration in the status of the object. This process includes acquisition, documentation, preservation, and often exhibition.</Note_Text>
